    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1914-07-12T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1914-07-12T00:00:00-05:00" n="1233"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1233">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 812.512/335.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Consul <persName type="from">Miller</persName> to the <gloss
                            type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">American Consulate</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Tampico</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-07-12">
                            <hi rend="italic">July 12, 1914</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Companies will have no difficulty to secure New York exchange, in fact all
                    remittances to Tampico offices are by New York exchange but the difficulty may
                    be to arrive at agreement with authorities as to what prevailing rate really is
                    in local transactions. Rate of July 11 ranged from 325 to 352 but local rate may
                    be governed somewhat by local conditions, production taxes must be paid by July
                    15. Probably would be fair to take the New York rate of July 13 on Carrancista
                    currency, and have arrangements made to have said rate wired to local custom
                    house and consulate said date and at stated intervals thereafter.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Miller</hi>
                    </signed>.</closer>
            </div>
        </body>
